<h2>
    Quick Tips for Eugene-Area Anglers
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Licenses required:</strong> Oregon angling license, Combined Angling Tag, and Columbia River Endorsement if fishing in Columbia tribs 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Timing matters:</strong> Fish during cooler spring and fall months, especially mornings/evenings.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Gear suggestions:</strong> Use 8–10 ft medium-heavy rods with 20–30 lb mainline and 12–15 lb leaders. Employ roe rigs, plugs, spinners, and small flashers.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Bank fishing is available in Eugene parks; boats are ideal for rivers like Siuslaw and Umpqua.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Check conditions &amp; regs:</strong> Always verify current openings, hatchery vs wild retention rules, barbless hook requirements on the ODFW website.
    </li>
</ul>

